    //heritage

  "heritage_title": "Exploring Heritage - Holy Family Trail",
  "heritage_hero_title": "Exploring Heritage",
  "heritage_hero_subtitle": "Discover the archaeological treasures that preserved the history of the Holy Family in Egypt",
  "heritage_about_title": "A Spiritual Journey Through History",
  "heritage_about_p1": "Embark on a journey through time and discover one of the oldest religious trails in the world, where faith blends with culture and nature in an eternal masterpiece. The Holy Family's trail in Egypt tells the legendary story of the Virgin Mary, the child Jesus, and Joseph the Carpenter's visit to the land of the Nile. This path crosses through sites with unique religious, historical, and archaeological significance, which have formed a cherished part of Egypt's identity over the centuries.\n\nIn this unique spiritual journey, churches and sacred monuments are scattered across more than 30 sites from North Sinai to southern Upper Egypt, each carrying a tale, preserving a memory, and reviving a tradition. With every step on this trail, you explore a rich heritage that reflects coexistence and tolerance among religions, showing how Egypt has been a safe haven for thousands of years.\nDiscover with us the deep roots of this trail, enjoy the beauty of nature, and immerse yourself in the living history that still thrives today.",
  "heritage_destinations_title": "Featured Places",
  "heritage_place1_title": "Virgin Mary Church - Al-Maadi",
  "heritage_place1_short_desc": "One of the most important sites where the Holy Family stopped.",
  "heritage_place1_details": "Did you know you're standing in a place where the child Jesus and the Virgin Mary rested? In the heart of Old Al-Maadi, a rocky hill rises, said to be the spot where the Virgin sat to nurse her child after a long journey from Palestine to Egypt.\n\nThe Virgin Mary Church in Al-Maadi is not just an archaeological site but a living witness to the story of faith and mercy, and an important stop for the Holy Family during their refuge in the land of the Nile.\nHere, the seeds of Christian faith in Egypt were planted, and here you can rediscover the past in all its details.",
  "heritage_place2_title": "Holy Family Cave - Abu Serga Church",
  "heritage_place2_short_desc": "The cave where the Holy Family hid during their stay in Egypt.",
  "heritage_place2_details": "Where the Holy Family found safety\nImagine yourself in the place where the Holy Family settled after a arduous journey from Palestine to Egypt.\nAbu Serga Church is not just a religious landmark but the most important station in the journey of the Virgin Mary, the child Jesus, and Saint Joseph in the heart of Old Fustat (southern Cairo today).\n\nThe church houses an ancient cave believed to be where the Holy Family lived for about three months, making it the oldest church built to commemorate Christ's presence in Egypt.\n\n✨ What makes this site unique:\n\nThe cave contains the rock from which water sprang when the child Jesus stepped on it.\nIt is one of the oldest churches in the world built on a site where Christ was present.\nIts distinctive architectural design reflects Coptic Christian history.",
  "heritage_place3_title": "The Cave Church - Jabal Al-Tair",
  "heritage_place3_short_desc": "A significant site believed to be visited by the Holy Family during their journey.",
  "heritage_place3_details": "Imagine a holy family fleeing persecution, seeking refuge in a cave within a towering mountain...\nIn the heart of Egypt's Western Desert, Jabal Al-Tair rises, believed to be where the Holy Family settled after entering Egypt. On this famous mountain, the Cave Church was built to commemorate this important spiritual station.\n\n✨ What makes this site exceptional:\n\nThe Holy Family is believed to have lived in this cave for several days.\nThe church was built inside the cave itself, commemorating Christ's presence in Egyptian land.\nThe site is surrounded by breathtaking natural beauty from all sides, making the visit a blend of faith and nature.\n📍 Discover the place where the Holy Family took shelter among the rocks...\nAt Jabal Al-Tair, heaven meets earth in a painting of faith and tranquility.\n\n👉 Are you seeking peace and spirituality?\nJabal Al-Tair awaits you!",
  "heritage_toggle_more": "Show more",
  "heritage_gallery_title": "Heritage Gallery",
  "heritage_cta_title": "Would you like to delve deeper into the Holy Family's heritage?",
  "heritage_cta_subtitle": "Plan your trip now and discover the archaeological treasures",
  "heritage_cta_btn": "Plan Your Trip",
"heritage_toggle_more": "Show more",
  "heritage_toggle_less": "Hide",
