  "local_cuisine_title": "Holy Family Trail - Taste Local Cuisine",
  "local_cuisine_hero_title": "Taste Local Cuisine",
  "local_cuisine_hero_subtitle": "A culinary journey through traditional dishes along the Holy Family Trail",
  "local_cuisine_section_title": "Traditional Cuisine Along the Trail",
  "local_cuisine_about_p1": "The Holy Family Trail passes through several regions in Egypt, each offering a unique set of traditional dishes that reflect the history and culture of the area. These cuisines form an integral part of the visitor's experience, presenting authentic local flavors passed down through generations.",
  "local_cuisine_about_p2": "From the Delta's dishes rich in fresh vegetables to the simple and delicious meals of Upper Egypt, the cuisine along the trail offers visitors an unforgettable culinary experience that harmonizes with their spiritual and historical journey.",
  "local_cuisine_regional_title": "Signature Dishes by Region",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_tab": "Sharqia and Delta",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_tab": "Cairo",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_tab": "Beheira",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_tab": "Minya and Asyut",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_title": "Sharqia and Delta Dishes",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_p1": "The Sharqia and Delta region is famous for dishes based on fresh agricultural products like Feteer Meshaltet, one of the most popular dishes in the area, which is a type of layered dough stuffed with honey, cheese, or meat.",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_p2": "Other distinctive dishes include:",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_li1": "Mumbar (stuffed intestines with rice and liver)",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_li2": "Fatta Baladi (bread with meat broth and garlic)",
  "local_cuisine_sharqia_li3": "Eastern Koshari (a mix of rice, pasta, and lentils)",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_title": "Cairo Dishes",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_p1": "Cairo offers a blend of all Egyptian cuisines but is particularly famous for some unique dishes like Koshari, one of the most popular street foods in Egypt, made of rice, pasta, lentils, and chickpeas with tomato sauce and fried onions.",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_p2": "Other distinctive dishes include:",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_li1": "Ful Medames (fava beans cooked with oil and lemon)",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_li2": "Taameya (Egyptian falafel)",
  "local_cuisine_cairo_li3": "Desserts like Kunafa and Qatayef",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_title": "Beheira Dishes",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_p1": "Beheira Governorate is known for some unique dishes like Feseekh (salted fish), a traditional dish for Sham El-Nessim, as well as dairy products from Wadi El Natrun.",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_p2": "Other distinctive dishes include:",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_li1": "Smoked herring",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_li2": "White cheese (especially from the monasteries of Wadi El Natrun)",
  "local_cuisine_beheira_li3": "Local pickles",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_title": "Minya and Asyut Dishes",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_p1": "Upper Egyptian cuisine, including Minya and Asyut, is characterized by simplicity and reliance on local ingredients like Fereek (green wheat) and grilled meats. One of the most famous dishes is Upper Egyptian Koshari, which differs from Cairo's version.",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_p2": "Other distinctive dishes include:",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_li1": "Upper Egyptian soup (lentil soup with cumin)",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_li2": "Upper Egyptian Fatta (with baladi bread and garlic)",
  "local_cuisine_asyut_li3": "Mahshi (stuffed vine leaves and cabbage)",
